# Server Provisioning

## Overview

This document outlines the procedures and best practices for provisioning new servers within the Automation Hub infrastructure.

## Prerequisites

- Access to provisioning automation tools
- Valid infrastructure templates
- Approved capacity request

## Provisioning Process

### 1. Preparation Phase
- Review capacity requirements
- Validate resource availability
- Prepare configuration templates

### 2. Deployment Phase
- Execute provisioning automation
- Monitor deployment progress
- Validate configuration compliance

### 3. Validation Phase
- Perform connectivity tests
- Verify security configurations
- Complete documentation updates

## Automation Tools

### Ansible Playbooks
- Infrastructure provisioning playbooks
- Configuration management roles
- Validation and testing scripts

### Terraform Modules
- Infrastructure templates
- Resource definitions
- State management

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues
- Network connectivity problems
- Resource quota limitations
- Template validation errors

### Resolution Steps
1. Check system logs
2. Validate prerequisites
3. Review configuration templates
4. Contact infrastructure team if needed
